   Noise Division (AEE-100)

   DRAFT Advisory Circular 36-4C

   Noise Standards: Aircraft Type and Airworthiness Certification

   The FAA is making a DRAFT version of the AC 36-4C available for the
   purpose of assisting interested persons who are reviewing the recently
   published noise certification standards for subsonic jet airplanes and
   subsonic transport category large airplanes NPRM [acrobat.gif] (July
   11, 2000).

   Below are the files containing the parts of the first DRAFT AC 36-4C.
     * Cover, Introduction, Definitions, and Table of Contents
       [acrobat.gif]
     * Chapter II-XI (Harmonized Subparts of Part 36) [acrobat.gif]
     * Chapter XII-XIII (Harmonized Appendices A and B) of Part 36
       [acrobat.gif]
     * Chapter XIV (Appendix F of Part 36, not covered in this AC)
     * Chapter XV (Harmonized Appendix G of Part 36) [acrobat.gif]
     * Appendices H and J are not included in the 1^st DRAFT of AC 36-4C
     * Appendix 1 (Environmental Technical Manual)
     * Appendix 2 (Volpe Center Certification Validation Package)
       [acrobat.gif]
     * Appendix 3 (Correction for the Effects of Background Noise)
       [acrobat.gif]
     * Supplement I to AC 36-4C [acrobat.gif]

   The above files may be modified as improvements are incorporated into
   DRAFT AC 36-4C.

   Last update: 8/9/00.
